  "title": "Why Applications Get Rejected",
  "text": "## CHUNK 8 — Why Applications Get Rejected\n\n### Why might my Axis Bank Credit Card application be rejected?\n\nCommon reasons for rejection include:\n\n- **Low CIBIL score** (below 700): Indicates past payment defaults or high credit utilization\n- **Insufficient income:** Salary below the card's minimum threshold\n- **High existing debt:** Multiple active loans or credit cards with high outstanding\n- **Employment instability:** Frequent job changes or self-employment without 2+ years of ITR\n- **Incomplete documents:** Missing PAN, income proof, or identity/address proof\n- **Previous defaults:** History of missed EMIs or credit card payments with any lender\n- **Address in a negative location:** Axis Bank maintains an internal negative area list\n\n> **Tip:** You can check your CIBIL score for free at cibil.com. Maintaining a score above 750 significantly improves approval chances.\n\n---"
