  "title": "Point Expiry and Account Closure",
  "text": "## CHUNK 9 — Point Expiry and Account Closure\n\n### Do EDGE Reward Points expire? What happens if I close my card?\n\n- **Expiry:** EDGE Reward Points are valid for **3 years** from the date of earning\n- **Card Closure:** Upon closure of your credit card account, all accumulated EDGE Reward Points are **forfeited** unless redeemed before closure\n- **Account Suspension:** Points may be frozen if your card account becomes delinquent (overdue payments)\n- **Checking Balance:** View your current EDGE points balance via Axis Mobile App → Cards → View Rewards, or via the EDGE portal\n\n> **Recommendation:** Redeem points before initiating card closure to avoid loss of accumulated rewards."
